{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17625145","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17625145"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T16:21:41+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T16:21:41+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17009"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17009","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17009"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.48,0.1,0.1,0.05,0.29]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9699"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"68227"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9699","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9699"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17009"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"53684"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"5326"},{"type":"tags","id":"5372"},{"type":"tags","id":"5418"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"22831"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22835"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"68227","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/68227"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EUltra-processed foods have become increasingly prevalent in modern diets worldwide. These products undergo multiple industrial processes and contain numerous ingredients.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the key characteristic of ultra-processed foods?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Made primarily from industrial food substances rather than whole foods","Made primarily through mechanical processing methods","Contains more than ten ingredients","Undergoes heat treatment above 100\u00b0C","Requires chemical preservation methods"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe key characteristic of ultra-processed foods is that they are \u003Cstrong\u003Emade primarily from industrial food substances rather than whole foods\u003C/strong\u003E. These products are formulated predominantly from substances derived from foods such as oils, fats, starches, isolated proteins, and include additives like preservatives, stabilizers, emulsifiers, and artificial flavours.\u003C/p\u003E            \u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E        \u003Cul\u003E                \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMade primarily through mechanical processing methods\u003C/strong\u003E - While mechanical processing may be involved, the defining characteristic is the use of industrial substances and additives\u003C/li\u003E                \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EContains more than ten ingredients\u003C/strong\u003E - While ultra-processed foods often contain many ingredients, this alone does not define them\u003C/li\u003E                \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EUndergoes heat treatment above 100\u00b0C\u003C/strong\u003E - High-temperature processing may occur but is not the defining characteristic\u003C/li\u003E                \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERequires chemical preservation methods\u003C/strong\u003E - While preservatives are common in ultra-processed foods, this is not their defining feature\u003C/li\u003E        \u003C/ul\u003E            \u003Cp\u003EAccording to the NOVA classification system, ultra-processed foods are Group 4 products that undergo multiple industrial processes and typically contain five or more ingredients, many of which are not available for home cooking.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Ultra-processed foods are industrial formulations made primarily from substances extracted from foods or synthesized from food substrates.","The NOVA food classification system categorizes ultra-processed foods as Group 4, characterized by extensive industrial processing and multiple ingredients.","Ultra-processed foods typically contain additives like preservatives, emulsifiers, sweeteners, and artificial flavours not commonly used in culinary preparation."],"references":["Lane MM, Gamage E, Du S, et al. Ultra-processed food exposure and adverse health outcomes: umbrella review of epidemiological meta-analyses. BMJ. 2024;384:e077310. Published 2024 Feb 28. doi:10.1136/bmj-2023-077310"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"53684"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17009"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"53684","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/53684"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-09T15:21:54+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-09T15:23:32+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9699"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"68227"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","sy